cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI 

The paper deals with detecting synthetic alterations in images, which is a problem related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning algorithms and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the adverse effects of such alterations on face recognition algorithms, which could fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) suggests that the paper could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
